The paper discusses the impact of increasing batch size on stochastic gradient descent for various network architectures and problem domains, which is a common topic in machine learning research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper specifically mentions image classification, image segmentation, and language modeling, which are all subfields of computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the impact of batch size on the computational cost and time to convergence, which are relevant topics in neural networks (cs.NE).
